* text=auto eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
*.bat text eol=crlf

# Vendored course content (synced from aptitude-course by scripts/sync_content.py;
# committed so the deploy image is reproducible and pin bumps are reviewable).
# The manifest schema/example beside it are first-party and NOT marked vendored.
# `-text` exempts the vendored bytes from the repo-wide `text=auto eol=lf`
# normalization: sync_content stamps a sha256 digest over the extracted bytes, so
# any eol rewrite on commit would make CONTENT_VERSION drift in CI (the bytes git
# checks out would differ from what was hashed). Store the pin verbatim.
backend/content/markdown/** linguist-vendored -text
backend/content/manifest.json linguist-vendored -text
backend/content/CONTENT_VERSION linguist-vendored -text
